<paragraph id="8BE23686FF9112191637F9D0D44ABD09" blockId="2.[264,1323,1593,1899]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<bibRefCitation id="EFCC4B77FF9112191637F9D0D537BC31" author="Metz" box="[264,538,1593,1619]" pageId="2" pageNumber="16" refString="Metz, M. A., Webb, D. W. &amp; Irwin, M. E. (2003) A review of the genus Psilocephala Zetterstedt (Diptera: Therevidae) with the description of four new genera. Studia Dipterologica, 10 (1), 227 - 266." type="journal article" year="2003">
Metz (Metz 
<emphasis id="B929EA94FF91121916A5F9D0D6F8BC30" box="[410,469,1593,1618]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al.</emphasis>
<number id="3D9524A1FF91121916E3F9D0D537BC31" box="[476,538,1593,1619]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number id="3D9524A1FF9112191521F9D0D561BC31" box="[542,588,1593,1619]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="239.0">239</number>
) provided an extensive diagnosis for 
<taxonomicName id="4C5D4D05FF9112191338F9D0D3BDBC30" box="[1031,1168,1593,1618]" class="Insecta" family="Therevidae" genus="Nigranitida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B929EA94FF9112191338F9D0D3BDBC30" box="[1031,1168,1593,1618]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Nigranitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The following additions to the diagnosis are based on the species circumscription defined in this revision: body length males 
<quantity id="4CA59B63FF9112191515F960D594BCC1" box="[554,697,1673,1699]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="6.7" metricValueMin="5.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="6.7" valueMin="5.3">5.3–6.7 mm</quantity>
(n= 
<number id="3D9524A1FF91121915D3F960D5D6BCC1" box="[748,763,1673,1699]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="9.0">9</number>
), females 
<quantity id="4CA59B63FF911219144AF960D32EBCC1" box="[885,1027,1673,1699]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.25" metricValueMax="8.8" metricValueMin="5.7" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="7.25" valueMax="8.8" valueMin="5.7">5.7–8.8 mm</quantity>
(n= 
<number id="3D9524A1FF9112191308F960D378BCC1" box="[1079,1109,1673,1699]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="14.0">14</number>
); male ommatidia smaller ventrally and laterally; male frons lacking setae; ventral lobe with ventral spines; distiphallus lacking apicolateral spines; ejaculatory apodeme bulbous posteriorly, in crosssection flattened dorsoventrally; furca (
<figureCitation id="13662A03FF91121915DFF8E8D415BD79" box="[736,824,1793,1819]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="5.[264,383,1524,1548]" captionTargetBox="[324,1256,293,1492]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[309,1265,281,1510]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Nigranitida costata 1. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view (MEI 048204). 2. Sternite 8, hypandrium, gonocoxite, ventral view. 3. Gonocoxite, hypandrium, dorsal view. 4. Gonocoxite, left lateral view. 5. Gonostylus, left lateral view. 6. Aedeagus, dorsal view (inset: ejaculatory apodeme cross­section). 7. Aedeagus, ventral view. 8. Aedeagus, left lateral view. 9. Female head. 10. Female internal reproductive organs (MEI 106765). Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: C = cercus, CD = common duct, DA = dorsal apodeme, Dp = distiphallus, EA = ejaculatory apodeme, Ep a = epandrium, F = furca, GA = gonocoxal apodeme, Gs = gonostylus, Gx = gonocoxite, GxB = gonocoxal bridge, H = hypandrium, Hp = hypoproct, Sp = spermatheca, SpD = spermathecal duct, SpS = spermathecal sac, SS = sensory seta, S 8 = sternite 8, T 8 = tergite 8, VA = ventral apodeme, VL = ventral lobe. Figure 9 modified from Metz et al, 2003." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158752/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Fig. 
<number id="3D9524A1FF9112191425F8E8D415BD79" box="[794,824,1793,1819]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
) oval, posterior margin rounded, anterior margin truncate; anterolateral projections short, posteromedial and anteromedial projections absent; spermathecal ducts directed anteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
